raw_data.title: Virtual Machine Cloud Implementation Specialist
raw_data.description: This role will provide cloud IT services to configure a virtual machine on the customer's network for a secure connection to the MRI(s) and PACS. This role has technical experience optimizing and configuring cloud systems, is competent in all phases of SwiftMR cloud system performance, and has knowledge of applicable hardware and software required to configure the virtual machine with the client’s existing infrastructure. The Virtual Machine Cloud Implementation Specialist is deployed for initial system implementation, and all associated hourly fees are purchased in conjunction with the Term – SwiftMR Cloud Deployment subscription packages.

raw_data.title: Gateway PC Cloud Implementation Specialist
raw_data.description: AIRS Medical will provide cloud IT services for Gateway PC installation, connection to Customer's network, MRI(s) and PACS. This role has technical experience optimizing and configuring cloud systems, is competent in all phases of SwiftMR system performance, and has knowledge of applicable hardware and software required to configure the Gateway PC with the client’s existing infrastructure. The Gateway PC Cloud Implementation Specialist is deployed for initial system implementation and all associated hourly fees are purchased in conjunction with the Term – SwiftMR Cloud Deployment subscription packages. The Gateway PC is provided to the Customer and must be returned to AIRS Medical in the same condition when applied, at the end of Cloud Deployment subscription term. Gateway PC destruction by the Customer is subject to additional fees.

raw_data.title: Virtual Consulting - SwiftMR Cloud Application Specialist
raw_data.description: The Customer may request virtual consulting support to be provided by a SwiftMR Cloud Application Specialist for additional protocol optimization outside of the Implementation Fee - Protocol Optimization scope of work (SOW). The SwiftMR Cloud Application Specialist is experienced in all aspects of the SwiftMR cloud technology and can provide advanced troubleshooting and configuration to the client. In addition, this role has knowledge of applicable software and hardware, such as MRI machines, and can provide protocol optimization across a wide range of imaging centers and hospitals.
